canonical_structure.name: UBX-LOG-RETRIEVEBATCH
canonical_structure.description: This message is used to request batched data.

bits.name: sendMonFirst
bits.description: Send UBX-MON-BATCH message before sending the UBX-LOG-BATCH message(s).

adjudication.reasoning: The message structure is identical across all three generations (M8, M9, M10). All three extractions captured the same data types, byte offsets, and bitfield definitions. The differences in 'message_type' ('input' vs 'command') are purely terminological conventions within different versions of the u-blox Interface Descriptions and do not represent a change in the protocol itself. The payload is consistently 4 bytes long with a 1-byte version, 1-byte bitfield, and 2-byte reserved padding.
